import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='total', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of total income across different regions?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Region")
    plt.ylabel("Total Income")
    plt.legend(title="Region", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate average income per person by region
    data['avg_income'] = data['total'] * data['pct']
    avg_income_by_region = data.groupby('region')['avg_income'].mean().reset_index()

    # Create bar chart
    ax = avg_income_by_region.plot.bar(x='region', y='avg_income', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the average income per person in each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Average Income per Person')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    # Add legend with colors
    for i, row in avg_income_by_region.iterrows():
        plt.text(i, row['avg_income'], f"{row['avg_income']:.2f}", ha='center', va='bottom')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).agg({'pct': 'sum'}).unstack()
    data_grouped.columns = data_grouped.columns.droplevel()
    
    ax = data_grouped.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income groups across different regions?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Region")
    plt.ylabel("Percentage")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Income Groups", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['total'], data['pct'], c=data['id'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('Total Population')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage of Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between income and percentage of population in each region?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Regions")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='name', columns='group', values='pct', aggfunc='sum')
    ax = data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(15, 8))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income groups for each state?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("State")
    plt.ylabel("Percentage")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Income Groups", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
